TITLE: Creating a Memorialized Actor Profile with Fedify (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates creating a new Person object with the memorial property set to true, using the Fedify library. By adding memorial: true, the actor's profile is displayed as memorialized within Mastodon-compatible platforms. Required dependency: @fedify/fedify. Key parameters include name, preferredUsername, summary, and optional attributes. The input is a configuration object, and the resulting Person is used to represent an ActivityPub actor.
SOURCE: https://github.com/fedify-dev/fedify/blob/main/docs/manual/pragmatics.md#2025-04-23_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { Person } from "@fedify/fedify";
// ---cut-before---
new Person({
  name: "Fedify Demo",
  preferredUsername: "demo",
  summary: "This is a Fedify Demo account",
  memorial: true,  // [!code highlight]
  // Other properties...
})
```

