TITLE: Resolving Collection Objects for Activity Recipients
DESCRIPTION: This code shows how to handle both actor and collection objects in the 'to' field of a Create activity. It recursively resolves collection objects to determine all recipients.
SOURCE: https://github.com/fedify-dev/fedify/blob/main/docs/manual/inbox.md#2025-04-23_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
.on(Create, async (ctx, create) => {
  for await (const to of create.getTos()) {
    if (isActor(to)) {
      // `to` is a recipient of the activity
      // Do something with the recipient
    } else if (to instanceof Collection) {
      // `to` is a collection object
      for await (const actor of to.getItems()) {
        if (!isActor(actor)) continue;
        // `actor` is a recipient of the activity
        // Do something with the recipient
      }
    }
  }
});
```

