TITLE: Implementing set() Method in Custom KvStore (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the implementation of the set() method for a custom KvStore. It stores a value with a given key, handling optional TTL (time-to-live) if the backend supports it.
SOURCE: https://github.com/fedify-dev/fedify/blob/main/docs/manual/kv.md#2025-04-23_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
async set(
  key: KvKey,
  value: unknown,
  options?: KvStoreSetOptions,
): Promise<void> {
  const serializedKey = this.serializeKey(key);
  if (options?.ttl == null) {
    await this.storage.set(serializedKey, value);
  } else {
    // Set with TTL if supported
    await this.storage.setWithTtl(
      serializedKey,
      value,
      options.ttl.total('millisecond'),
    );
  }
}
```

