TITLE: Configuring WebFinger Links with Custom URL Property in Fedify (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to set up an actor dispatcher in Fedify with custom URL properties. It demonstrates how to provide multiple links with different 'rel' values in the WebFinger response, including profile page, alternate formats, and OpenID issuer.
SOURCE: https://github.com/fedify-dev/fedify/blob/main/docs/manual/actor.md#2025-04-23_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
federation
  .setActorDispatcher("/users/{identifier}", async (ctx, identifier) => {
    return new Person({
      id: ctx.getActorUri(identifier),
      preferredUsername: identifier,
      urls: [
        new URL(`/@${identifier}`, ctx.origin),
        new Link({
          rel: "alternate",
          href: new URL(`/@${identifier}/atom.xml`, ctx.origin),
          mediaType: "application/atom+xml",
        }),
        new Link({
          rel: "http://openid.net/specs/connect/1.0/issuer",
          href: new URL("/openid", ctx.origin),
        }),
      ],
      // Omitted for brevity; see the previous example for details.
    });
  });
```

